name: Gargoyle-4-de_Blaine
description:
Gargoyle du Château de Blaine (Loire-Atlantique)
The white-eyed brother, who looks like a clown, has a bell. Are you laughing at human stupidity or is it a warning, like a wolf boy who doesn't know if it's a lie or true?

The gargoyle is an image of the forces of chaos located on the periphery of the world, the embodiment of the demonic principle, subject to the highest divine will. They are an integral part of the idea of an ordered universe as having overcome the stage of chaos; placed in the service of angels or other divine characters.
